authorMeta.name: orcaedits4
text:
Rest in peace, Katina❤️

Katina was 50 years old, she lived at SeaWorld Orlando, she lived with Malia, her calves, Nalani and Makaio and her grandchild Trua. 50 years is an exceptional age for a female orca especially in captivity, she was healthy and thriving. Her story was an inspiration that I hope will be remembered for years to come.

Katina was captured in Iceland in 1978, she was later moved to Marineland Canada in which she spent time with Kanduke, Nootka and Kandu ii, they would live together for many months. In 1979 SeaWorld Ohio made the decision to purchase Katina, but she only lived there for summer seasons whilst the park was open, in other months she lived at SeaWorld San Diego. This pattern repeat, with her eventually ending up in SeaWorld Orlando.

In Orlando Katina gave birth to Kalina, the first orca to ever successfully survive in human care, this made history and news was spread worldwide. Katina would end up with more calves sired by various males. Katerina was born in 1988, Taku in 1993, Unna in 1996, Ikaika in 2002, Nalani in 2006 and her final calf Makaio in 2010. Many of these calves were separated from her and she never saw them again. Ikaika, Nalani and Makaio are her only surviving offspring. But it’s safe to say Katina played a huge impact with her genes in captivity, she shaped SeaWorld to what it is today.

In 2016 a breeding ban was put into place which meant males and females had to be separated. This especially took a toll on Katina, she was often seen vocalising to her son, Makaio through the gates wanting to interact with him, but not being able to. Throughout the years the males and females could reunite very rarely if they weren’t cycling, but this slowed down over time, with the last close contact being in 2022. 

Katina developed an illness recently causing visible skin lesions, very similar to how Kasatka looked at times. Although this did not stop Katina, she kept participating in shows whenever she felt like it, making surprise appearances, even if was just swimming really slow around the show pool. She wanted to be included, and the matriarch always gets what she wants.

Today, Katina was humanely euthanised by SeaWorld’s veterinary team. The choice was made to prioritise her quality of life. She passed with trainers and vets around her side, some who have known her for decades, she was not alone during this. 

Euthanasia is an extremely hard decision and I cannot imagine how staff must be feeling right now, my heart goes out to them and the other orcas at Orlando. Their pod has been torn apart and it may never recover.

I had first heard rumours of Katina’s passing, it was a very stressful hour chatting with others about whether it is true or not, until finally SeaWorld made the post we all dreaded. 

Katina was a dear orca to me, she was incredibly special and I longed to meet her someday, the way she breached as if she was a soaring eagle was nothing less than extraordinary, her age never changed her. Katina was ever the cutest whale who could surely put a smile on anyone’s faces, I had never even met her in person and yet I still feel so deeply. She will not be forgotten, her tale is one that will last, her children are here, she will forever live through them. 

I don’t think it’s a coincidence she passed on the 10th anniversary of Unna’s death. Her daughter has waited so long. No mother can resist her child’s call.

Dearest Katina, you have changed a part of me and I don’t think I can thank you enough for  that, may you play with your family once again, perhaps you can show them your home waters and teach them to fly through the starry skies. We love you Tina and we always will.

Merry Christmas Katina, we’ll see you again❤️
.

Dừa Xiêm Dẻ Cười - Hành trình vị giác mới lạ với sự kết hợp độc đáo 🥥💚

Lần đầu tiên, Nước Dừa Xiêm thanh ngọt được KATINAT khéo léo kết hợp hài hoà với Trà Xanh Nhài tinh tuyển từ vùng Tây Bắc, mang đến hành trình trải nghiệm vị giác tinh tế, đầy cảm hứng.

Từng tầng hương vị của Dừa Xiêm Dẻ Cười được đánh thức từ lớp kem Hạt Dẻ Cười béo thơm, điểm xuyết cùng Hạt Dẻ rang giòn bùi bắt miệng. Trải nghiệm thưởng thức trở nên trọn vẹn bởi sự thanh khiết từ nền Trà Xanh Nhài chát nhẹ, quyện cùng vị ngọt lành của Nước Dừa Xiêm, nhẹ nhàng để lại dư vị hài hoà, ấn tượng.

Ghé ngay KATINAT và tận hưởng phong vị Giáng Sinh mới toanh với Dừa Xiêm Dẻ Cười nhé Katies ơi! 💗#katinatcantho #xuhuong #fypシ゚ #katinat #cantho

authorMeta.name: kat.quintana
text:
Have you hit a plateau? There are multiple ways you can reinvigorate your content marketing strategy! I’ll touch on 3 for now.

Keep in mind, my preference is to incorporate all 3 approaches at once. I believe this mix gives you room to stay creative & strategic.

✺ Meeting content quotas
To get yourself out of a content slump & start selling your offers consistently, you might consider weekly or monthly goals that define the number of posts you’ll share on each of your digital platforms.

Warning: If you sense that these content quotas might give you an excuse to just post – but not post *well* – then perhaps you should steer away from huge content quotas.

✺ Learning from competitors w/o copying
While it’s tempting to replicate successful strategies used by competitors, it’s vital to differentiate between research & plagiarism. Copying someone else’s work not only hampers your creativity but also risks legal disputes.

Instead, view competitors’ content as inspiration, learning from their tactics & adapting them to create a unique message.

Keyword: “adapting.”

When you view your content marketing strategy as one big experiment, you allow yourself to have more fun with the creative process that ultimately leads to the substantial revenue you’ve been aiming for.

✺ Analyzing & enhancing creativity
Don’t be afraid of analyzing your past metrics. Dive into Google Analytics & social media insights to uncover patterns & develop hypotheses about what engages your audience.

But but buuut…don’t simply repeat past successes – add a creative & timely twist to keep your content fresh & appealing.

Even if this means deviating from your original monthly content plan, it’s worth it to reach the right audience effectively.

At the same time, certain aspects of your content *should* remain consistent:

✺ Brand voice: Maintain a consistent tone & style in your messaging.

✺ Brand values: Align your content with your brand’s core values.

Pretty like  Manon in my Katseye gnarly @@KATSEYE@@daniela avanzini@@meret manon##xbcyza##katseye##fyppppppppppppppppppppppp##trending##katseyemanonKatseye (pronounced "cat's eye", stylized in all caps) is a girl group based in Los Angeles. The group is composed of six members: Daniela Avanzini, Lara Raj, Manon Bannerman, Megan Skiendiel, Sophia Laforteza, and Yoonchae Jeung. With members from the Philippines, South Korea, Switzerland, and the United States, Katseye is often described as a "global girl group".

The group was formed through the 2023 reality competition series Dream Academy, a collaboration between Hybe and Geffen Records. The group's formation process was later chronicled in the Netflix docuseries Popstar Academy: Katseye, which recounted the audition process, intensive training, and formation of the group. Katseye debuted in June 2024 with the single "Debut", followed by their breakthrough single, "Touch". They released their first extended play (EP), SIS (Soft Is Strong), later that year. In April 2025, they released "Gnarly" which served as the lead single for their second EP, Beautiful Chaos (2025). Despite receiving mixed reactions on release, the single garnered significant attention and earned the group their first entry on the Billboard Hot 100. Beautiful Chaos was released on June 27, 2025, and debuted at number four on the Billboard 200, their highest-charting release to date. The EP's second single "Gabriela" peaked within the top 40 of the Hot 100 and earned a Grammy Award nomination for Best Pop Duo/Group Performance, with the group also being nominated for Best New Artist at the 68th Annual Grammy Awards.
Katseye is recognized for their distinctive fashion identity, prominently drawing influence from Y2K fashion. Their growing brand image has led to multiple endorsements and campaigns tying into the style, including a campaign with Fendi's Baguette bag and Gap's low-rise denim. Katseye has also worked with British soap company Lush, American fashion house Coach, and Filipino fast food chain Jollibee. Humberto Leon acts as the group's creative director, taking inspiration from broad influences and utilizing the group's diverse backgrounds.

authorMeta.name: katinat.hothitu
text:
Năm cũ khép lại, năm mới gõ cửa ✨
Katinat Hồ Thị Tư vẫn ở đây, vẫn những gương mặt quen đã cùng nhau đi qua bao ca làm, bao áp lực, bao tiếng cười, và năm nay lại vui hơn khi chào đón thêm những gương mặt mới cùng chung một mái nhà ☕️🤍
Quen mà không cũ, mới mà vẫn rất thân.
Mỗi ngày ở Katinat không chỉ là công việc, mà là những ly cà phê pha bằng sự chỉn chu, là những buổi chạy ca bận rộn nhưng luôn có nhau hỗ trợ, là những khoảnh khắc rất đời – rất thật – rất đáng nhớ 🌿
Năm mới rồi, mong là chúng ta vẫn đồng hành cùng nhau ở đây, vẫn giữ tinh thần trách nhiệm quen thuộc, nhưng mang theo thật nhiều năng lượng tích cực và niềm vui mới ✨
Katinat Hồ Thị Tư – không chỉ là nơi làm việc, mà là nơi tụi mình cùng nhau lớn lên mỗi ngày ❤️ #katinat #thanhtuu2025
